      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Letting go doesn't mean erasing who you are, but it means stopping the desperate clinging to a version of yourself that can only exist when he is there. You are not a shell; you are a person who has been broken, and the only way to stop the pain of trying to fix a broken thing is to let it break completely so it can be rebuilt from scratch. Yes, it is supposed to be this hard, but the pain of staying is far worse than the pain of finally ending the struggle.",
